Text.SourceString: Oh, nice to meet you too!//<portrait=happy>My name’s <NPCName>Everest</>…//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Eva</> for short.
We don’t see too many new faces, so your arrival is great for the town.
Do you think they’ll ever open another bakery in town?
Oh, I’m not scared!//<portrait=normal>I think it would be amazing. I’d love to meet other bakers.
Do you think they’ll ever open another bakery in town?
Oh, I’m not scared!//<portrait=normal>I think it would be amazing. I’d love to meet other bakers.
I feel so awful for stray animals…//<portrait=sad>I wish we could build them little houses in the woods.
Hmm… Yeah, there are plenty of trees and rocks for them to take shelter under.//<portrait=sad>You’re right.//But still.
What if someone built a big mansion where the recycling center is?
The vineyard view alone! Wow!//<portrait=happy>And right next to the community center.
I feel so awful for stray animals…//<portrait=sad>I wish we could build them little houses in the woods.
Hmm… Yeah, there are plenty of trees and rocks for them to take shelter under.//<portrait=sad>You’re right.//But still.
Aww… You were at Sam’s looking for me?//<portrait=normal>Today is my day off, actually.
I like to spend my days off hanging around in the park, or hiking somewhere pretty.
I have lots of dreams. I don't know where to begin.//<portrait=normal>For instance, I would love to open my own bakery someday. Once I master pies and cakes.
I’m glad <NpcName>Randy</> is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four students.
Let’s just hope the government doesn’t close down the school the first chance they get.
Do you smell that? That's no perfume.//<portrait=normal>You’re smelling the cookies I baked.
Oh, I don’t mind at all! I love baking.//<portrait=normal>Besides, I get to keep some of them for myself.
How are you doing today?
I work regular hours today.//No big deal, though. I like baking.
Also, I get to come out of the kitchen smelling like cookies.//<portrait=normal>Who doesn’t love that?!
Hello, neighbor!//Another Wednesday, eh?
The food here is so yum.//Lodeh, popiah, fried rice… I have to teach myself to make those, one of these days.
*sighs*
Aww… You were at Sam’s looking for me?//<portrait=annoyed>Oh no. Wednesday is my day off.
Umm… No baking for me today.//<portrait=normal>I would rather spend my day off hanging around in the park, or knitting something pretty.
I love the lake in Winter, when everything is rigid and frozen.//It looks so clean and pretty.//Mesmerizing to look at.
Sundays are special for me.//<portrait=happy>I hang out at the Tavern with <NpcName>Betty</> after work. Girls’ night in…//Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.
I love how <NpcName>Betty</> and I can just talk and talk about baking…//And red velvet.//Turns out we have a lot in common!
You found me!//<portrait=normal>What’s up?
I opened my window this morning, and the mist woke me right up.
Oh! I just love your style!//<portrait=normal>I like to pay attention to people’s outfits around here. You know, for inspiration.
I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith.//<portrait=concerned>You moved to an island and totally changed career paths.
I don’t think I could ever do that…//<portrait=sad>Not brave enough.
Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that.//I hope I didn’t bum you out.
I’m glad <NpcName>Randy</> is fighting to keep our school open, even though we only have four students.
Let’s just hope the government doesn’t close down the school the first chance they get.
The food here makes me miss my parents.//Ah, you too, huh?
*sighs*
Red velvet cakes at Fishensips is so yum!//I don’t know what I would do if <NpcName>Frank</> stopped making red velvet cakes.
I’ve tried copying <NpcName>Frank</>’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine are never as good…

For some reason I always crave red velvet cake on Fridays.//<portrait=normal>You know, maybe it’s a celebratory thing. Maybe…//<portrait=annoyed>In my mind, red velvet cake marks the end of the week.//I don’t know.
Hmm… Do you think there’s, like, a green velvet cake?//<portrait=happy>Should I try making one with lettuce?//<portrait=annoyed>Doesn’t sound very appealing, to be honest.
Sundays are special for me.//<portrait=happy>I hang out at the Tavern with <NpcName>Betty</> after work. Girls’ night in…//Just a couple of bakers, chatting the night away.
I love how <NpcName>Betty</> and I can just talk and talk about baking…//And red velvet.//Turns out we have a lot in common!
I work regular hours today.//No big deal, though. I like baking.
There’s nothing else I can do around here, anyway. So I might as well bake.//<portrait=happy>Besides, baking is fun.
Red velvet cakes at Fishensips is so yum!//I don’t know what I would do if <NpcName>Frank</> stopped making red velvet cakes.
I’ve tried copying <NpcName>Frank</>’s red velvet cakes many times, but mine are never as good…
<NpcName>Macy</> is the one who has a cool pet lobster…not me.//Well, it’s not much of a pet, really. More like a rescue.//<portrait=happy>Pretty eccentric gal, she is.
<NpcName>Macy</> loves pizza and wine.//She said they remind her of home.//I think she’s pretty close with her folks. She talks about home a lot.
I gotta say, I envy your courage for taking a leap of faith.//<portrait=concerned>You moved to an island and totally changed career paths.
I don’t think I could ever do that…//<portrait=sad>Not brave enough.
Ugh, sorry. I don’t know why I said that.//I hope I didn’t bum you out.
You must be busy on Mondays, huh?//Running a farm as big as yours must take a lot.
Not just energy.//It takes a lot of patience and dedication, I’m sure.
What are you up to, <PlayerName>$player</>?
I sew after work.//Ah, for fun. The inn has a community sewing machine in the lobby, so why not?
Many things… But I mostly sew decorative pillows.//<portrait=happy>They’re gorgeous and easy to make.
Decorative pillows are so expensive. That’s why I’m making my own.
So true, decorative pillows are impractical.//<portrait=normal>But they look so pretty on the furniture! Can’t help myself.
Just working… Then I’ll watch some TV, then rest.//<portrait=concerned>Sounds so dull when I say it out loud.
Can your farm make truffle oil?//<portrait=happy>The mayor loves it, by the way. He said it’s the secret ingredient in <NpcName>Carol</>’s stew.
Oh… Haven’t you heard? <NpcName>Carol</> is Mayor <NpcName>Connor</>’s late wife.//<portrait=sad>May she rest in peace.
I had a slice of bread for a quick breakfast this morning.//That and some fruit from the kitchen.
There are still things I want to see in this world.//Like, I’m sure there’s more to life than baking cookies.
Maybe farming…or swimming with dolphins.//<portrait=normal>Go hiking up the mountain and see the stars up close. I haven’t done any of those things just yet.
I work from noon to five on Sundays.//What about you?
Can your farm make truffle oil?//<portrait=happy>The mayor loves it, by the way. He said it’s the secret ingredient in <NpcName>Carol</>’s stew.
Oh… Haven’t you heard? <NpcName>Carol</> is Mayor <NpcName>Connor</>’s late wife.//<portrait=sad>May she rest in peace.
Are you done for the day?//I don’t know how big a workload farmers have.
Do you like to visit the museum?//I see you go in and out of there pretty often.
Oh, gotcha. Me neither… It’s too quiet for my taste.//<portrait=concerned>It would put me right to sleep.
Oh gosh. I keep running into you, <PlayerName>$player</>. What a fun thing to happen.
What type of movies do you like?

Ah, I see… I’m too scared to watch thrillers. <NpcName>Suki</> held a thriller party where we all watched this movie about a madman in a mask, raging around with a chainsaw, and I had to sleep with my lights on for two days.
Oh yes! We should watch a stand-up comedian together sometime.
Ah, my kind of friend! I love romantic movies too. We should totally have a red velvet party and binge on rom-coms sometime.
Ugh… My room is such a mess right now. I should clean it up.
Unless she needs to pick up some groceries, I rarely see <NpcName>Zarah</> in the shop.//It seems she’s not a big vegetable buyer, either, ’cause I mostly see her buying a bunch of flour and oil.
I don’t really know <NpcName>Zarah</> that well. She loves cookies, though.//She buys them in bulk.
Oh gosh. I keep running into you, <PlayerName>$player</>. What a fun thing to happen!
Unless she needs to pick up some groceries, I rarely see <NpcName>Zarah</> in the shop.//It seems she’s not a big vegetable buyer, either, ’cause I mostly see her buying a bunch of flour and oil.
I don’t really know <NpcName>Zarah</> that well. She loves cookies, though.//She buys them in bulk.
Err… No. I don’t sing if I don’t have to. I bet you sound good, though. I’ll have to hear you sometime.
I love to read about traveling, to learn what the world is like out there. Maybe one day I’ll go and see for myself.
Maybe, maybe, maybe… With the never-ending bills, it’s hard to know when that might be.
I love to read about traveling, to learn what the world is like out there. Maybe one day I’ll go and see for myself.
Maybe, maybe, maybe… With the never-ending bills, it’s hard to know when that might be.
I can bake more things, you know. Not just cookies and bread.
Hmm… Let’s see. Pineapple upside-down cake, pumpkin pies, doughnuts! Hmm… What else?
Well, if I had to choose, cookies are probably my best baked goods. I make them all the time, so I think I might have maxed out my cookie-baking skills.
Practice does make perfect. Maybe if <NpcName>Sam</> starts selling other things, like pies, I can finally get good at baking pies too.
I can’t just start baking a whole bunch of cakes and pies at the inn.//I mean, who’s going to eat them?
Also, I don’t want to buy ingredients for pies that nobody will eat, just to improve my baking skills.//Seems a tad wasteful to me.
Ugh… So much negativity. Sorry for attacking you like that, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s you again. How fun.
I think I’ll go see <NpcName>Betty</> at the Tavern tomorrow. Why?
I haven’t planned it yet.
I can’t just start baking a whole bunch of cakes and pies at the inn.//I mean, who’s going to eat them?
Also, I don’t want to buy ingredients for pies that nobody will eat, just to improve my baking skills.
Ugh… So much negativity. Sorry for attacking you like that, <PlayerName>$player</>.
How’s your first Spring on Coral Island so far?
I often find wasabi sprouting this time of year, near the lake.//<portrait=happy>Have you found any yet?
I often find wasabi sprouting this time of year, near the lake.//<portrait=happy>Have you found any yet?
The beach is still a little cold.//Have you ever found anything pretty, diving here?//<portrait=surprised>You have?!
<NpcName>Theo</> showed me a handful of jade a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>He told me he got it from an old treasure chest.
The beach is still a little cold.//Have you ever found anything pretty, diving here?//<portrait=surprised>You have?!
<NpcName>Theo</> showed me a handful of jade a long time ago.//<portrait=happy>He told me he got it from an old treasure chest.
With Summer right around the corner, it must be a busy period for you as a farmer, huh?
I’m not sure if you noticed, but the grass changes color a bit in Summer.//Nature is beautiful, isn’t it?
Peonies are the prettiest flower in the world, don’t you think?//<portrait=normal>Their blossoms are so large, and their colors are blindingly vivid.
Too bad they only bloom in Spring.
The snow melts so fast.//It’s already gone, and Spring just started!
I can’t wait for the Cherry Blossom Festival. It’ll be so much fun. I might try my luck with balap karung this year… I don’t know! Maybeeeee!
Are you going to plant flowers on your farm?//If you do, just don’t give any to <NPCName>Charles</>. He has some sort of pollen sensitivity.
Coral Island is just so beautiful in Spring. I’m glad I moved here.
I prefer Spring to Summer… But if we’re talking favorites, it would definitely be Winter.//It’s more bearable working in front of the oven in Winter.
What do you think would be the perfect baked good for Spring?//<portrait=happy>For me, probably something colorful like a fruit tart. So yum!
The inn doesn’t have a working air conditioner.//It sort of turns on and off by itself sometimes. My room can get pretty hot.
I grew up with this type of weather…hot and humid basically all year long.//So yeah, I’m used to it, but working in front of the oven in this weather is still…something.
So glad I picked this blouse today.//It’s nice and breezy!
The Beach Cleanup Festival is right in front of the inn.//I wake up to people getting the festival ready…on the 27th of Summer, of course! Not today. Ha ha!

It’s not bad living at the inn, the second floor especially… Yeah, it does get really hot in Summer because of the broken air conditioner.//<portrait=normal>But after sunset, you open the window, and the salty breeze is just divine!

I might enter the swimming contest next week. It’ll be fun, even if I’m not a great swimmer. Especially compared to <NPCName>Sunny</>!//<portrait=surprised>He doesn’t move that fast when he’s walking!
Have you seen those cute little white flowers growing everywhere?//What are those? I think they’re daisies.//Are they daisies, you think?
Isn’t this the best season for cookies and tea?
Fall is so pretty, isn’t it? Back home, the trees never looked like this.
The Harvest Festival here is so cool.//It’s nothing like the one we had when I was growing up.
It is a bit chilly right now, but I much prefer it to the heat of Summer.
It’s getting colder, isn’t it? I guess it’s a sign Winter is just around the corner.
Fall is one of the reasons I decided to move here. It’s the most beautiful thing I’ve ever seen.//<portrait=happy>And who wouldn’t want to wake up to see that every day?
I want to bake some pumpkin pies. Might as well since they’re in season, right?
I hardly ever baked pumpkin pies until I moved here. I was missing out!
I love snow, you know. It’s so fascinating the way it’s soft and fluffy but also cold and clumpy.//It feels magical.
I don’t think I’ll ever get bored with snow. I didn’t grow up with it, so I always find it mesmerizing.
Better make sure my heater works. The inn’s central heating isn’t warm enough for me.//<portrait=surprised>Oh, but don’t tell <NPCName>Suki</>! She can be scary sometimes...
These are the days when I’m super glad I’m a baker. I have my own personal heater at work!
You look all nice and cozy today.
I usually don’t notice how much heat the oven at <NPCName>Sam’s</> radiates until it’s Summer.//<PlayerName>$player</>, it’s really hot!
Winter is the perfect time to slow down a little…//Reflect on the year and stuff.
I kind of want to play in the snow in the park with the kids. <NPCName>Valentina</> always looks like she’s having so much fun playing outside.
I’m grateful for everything that I have, but living by the sea isn’t as fun as it sounds…//Especially in Summer.
I know… I know…//<portrait=concerned>I sound like a brat, but it gets so humid, my hair doubles in size.
When I have the time, I’ll forage around the woodlands for some fresh Summer veggies and flowers.
The best is when I find jackfruit.//<portrait=normal>I always share some with <NpcName>Bree</>, the wine lady. She loves to make a fancy meal out of it.
When I have the time, I’ll forage around the woodlands for some fresh Summer veggies and flowers.
The best is when I find jackfruit.//<portrait=normal>I always share some with <NpcName>Bree</>, the wine lady. She loves to make a fancy meal out of it.
<NpcName>Bree</> makes a delicious shredded jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry! It’s vegan, in case you are.
<NpcName>Bree</> makes a delicious shredded jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry! It’s vegan, in case you are.
<NpcName>Bree</> makes a delicious shredded jackfruit pie.//<portrait=happy>Oh, don’t worry! It’s vegan, in case you are.
Oh, almost forget to mention.//<portrait=normal>Did you know that you can find shallots around the lake this time of year?
You can find shallots around the lake this time of year, you know! Have you found any yet?
I’m grateful for everything that I have, but living by the sea isn’t as fun as it sounds… Especially in Summer.
I know… I know… I sound like a brat, but it gets so humid, my hair doubles in size.

My favorite festivals are the Animal Festival and Harvest Festival!//I like the Cherry Blossom Festival potluck too. It’s just that it’s always held so early in Spring. It’s still so cold to be outside all day.
I love Summer, but I’m ready for it to cool down a little.
I’m so ready for some green tea and cookie weather.
I love summer, but I’m ready for it to cool down a little.
I’m so ready for some green tea and cookie weather.
The leaves were so crunchy when I walked to work this morning. They were so satisfying to step on.
Oh, come on! You’re telling me that you’ve never gone out of your way to find a pile of crunchy leaves, just to step on them?
I can only imagine how misty it gets in the morning at the farm, this time of year. What a perfect way to start your day.
The leaves were so crunchy when I walked to work this morning. They were so satisfying to step on.
Oh, come on! You’re telling me that you’ve never gone out of your way to find a pile of crunchy leaves, just to step on them?
I can only imagine how misty it gets in the morning at the farm, this time of year. What a perfect way to start your day.
I’m turning on my heater tonight. It’s starting to get too cold for me. The central heat at the inn just isn’t cutting it.
I can only imagine how cozy the nights are at the farm, this time of year. What a perfect way to end your day.
I don’t eat out much. I don’t know… I guess the dishes that I actually love, I can make myself.
<NpcName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Betty</> still have the best red velvet cake in town, though.
When the snow blankets the town like this, it’s hard to tell the buildings apart. Until you go inside, you don’t know whose house it really is.
A beautiful analogy to remind us not to judge one another, I think.
I always get all sappy during Winter. Argh…
I always get all sappy during Winter. Argh…
I always get all sappy during Winter. Argh…
When the snow blankets the town like this, it’s hard to tell the buildings apart. Until you go inside, you don’t know whose house it really is.
A beautiful analogy to remind us not to judge one another, I think.
One day I want to throw fancy parties, like <NpcName>Bree</>’s annual dinner parties. Ah, you know! With a dress code and an elaborate theme, and stuff.
Oh yes! A party where we all can eat fancy food and sip fine drinks. Oh, and everybody has a great time. That would be fabulous.
Be careful out there. The path might be slippery.
I’m not going to hike today. I’m afraid I might trip.
Oh my! Stop teasing.//Not a joke, I was being serious.
It’s nice and warm here.//Hmm…
Going somewhere?//Nobody likes getting wet. Please excuse me.
Why do rainy nights always make me feel sooooo melancholy…
Oh my.
I hope I can borrow a couple of extra blankets tonight from <NPCName>Suki</>.
It’s getting late, <PlayerName>$player</>.//You should really go home and rest.
Be careful out there. The path might be slippery.
I’m not going to hike today. I’m afraid I might trip.
Oh my! Stop teasing.//Not a joke, I was being serious.
It’s nice and warm here.//Hmm…
Going somewhere?//Nobody likes getting wet. Please excuse me.
Why do rainy nights always make me feel sooooo melancholy…
Oh my.
I hope I can borrow a couple of extra blankets tonight from <NPCName>Suki</>.
It’s getting late, <PlayerName>$player</>. You should really go home and rest.
It doesn’t snow back home… Umm…
I don’t know why I keep telling you that. Oops.
Does it snow back in Pokyo, <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’ve never been there.
*shivering* I need to stand near the fireplace.//<portrait=sad>I’m not built for this type of weather.
*shivering* I need to stand near the fireplace.//<portrait=sad>I’m not built for this type of weather.
Today was a long day! With the snow and all.//<portrait=sad>Good gosh.
Wow… With snow like this, you can really see everyone’s footprints!//Which ones are yours?
Wow… With snow like this, you can really see everyone’s footprints!//Which ones are yours?
It’s either fluffy or slippery this time of year. You really have to be careful going back, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Should I build a snowman today?//I mean, this is definitely the weather for it.
When the snow blankets the town like this, it’s hard to tell the buildings apart.//Until you go inside, you don’t know whose house it really is.
A beautiful analogy to remind us not to judge one another, I think.
I always get all sappy during Winter. Aww…
The baked goods here are freshly baked every day.//Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>. I can vouch for this because I bake them myself.
<NpcName>Sam</> always makes sure we only use the best ingredients.//He believes that people can taste quality, and I kind of agree with him on that.
<NpcName>Sam</> is a great boss. He may seem off-putting at first, but he’s actually really kind.//<portrait=concerned>He is direct, though… Yeah.
I’m making fruit tart today.//I used fresh blueberries, but you can use literally any fruit.
Someday I want to have a big house, with a big kitchen to chop vegetables in. You know?!
Oh gosh. One with big glass windows on the side!//<portrait=normal>And a bunch of fancy paintings hanging around my kitchen.
Starlet is such a beautiful town, and I think people truly care about each other here.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it.
Growing up, my parents told me that if you have people who care about you, you have a good life.
I’m starting to see what they meant.
Starlet is such a beautiful town, and I think people truly care about each other here.//<portrait=happy>I can feel it.
Growing up, my parents told me that if you have people who care about you, you have a good life.
I’m starting to see what they meant.
I mean, look at this town…//<portrait=happy>We have a tavern right there.//The beach is that way…//<portrait=normal>And we have a fully stocked library right there.
<NpcName>Sam</>’s best quality is that he is direct. Other than that, he’s very…//<portrait=concerned>You know. Umm…
Umm… <NpcName>Sam</> is straightforward, honest.//<portrait=annoyed>Frank, direct.//Did I say direct already?
I have extra food in the kitchen if you’re hungry.
I don’t really like tidying up.//It’s a waste of time, and let’s face it, it’s going to get messy again anyway.
Someday I want to have a big house, with a big kitchen to chop vegetables in. You know?!
Oh gosh. One with big glass windows on the side!//<portrait=normal>And a bunch of fancy paintings hanging around my kitchen.
A girl can dream, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I don’t eat out much.//I don’t know… I guess the dishes that I actually love, I can make myself.
<NpcName>Frank</> and <NpcName>Betty</> still have the best red velvet cake in town, though.
Ah, it’s nice to go out every once in a while and not have to cook.
Now, this is my kind of music!
Are you foraging for wild mushrooms too?
Do you ever feel like you’re doing a lot, but no matter what, it’s just not enough?
But I’m grateful that I have all of you as my family.
<PlayerName>$player</>, you came from Pokyo, right? That’s so interesting! What was it like in the big city?
Oh. Well, um, I’m glad you’re here now!

Special.SourceString: Loud, smelly, and full of tourists.

Text.SourceString: It sounds amazing. I bet you’d be a great tour guide!
Oh… ha ha. I can understand that.
If you could travel anywhere in the world, what would you do first?
Oh, that sounds amazing! Conservation is so important, too, especially in this day and age. Good pick!

Special.SourceString: Go on an eco-tour of a beautiful wilderness

Text.SourceString: Wow, what I wouldn’t give… Those shows must be breathtaking. Good pick!

Special.SourceString: Attend a performance at a prestigeous theatre

Text.SourceString: Ooh, I’m hungry just thinking about that. Great pick!

Special.SourceString: Travel the continent, trying all the foods I can

Text.SourceString: Really? I can’t imagine not wanting to see the world…but okay.
You must have a really interesting perspective on the world!//<portrait=happy>You went from a big city to a farm on an island, and all that.
I’ve always been interested in baking!//I only started doing it professionally a few years ago, though.
<NpcName>Sam</> needed a baker, I needed a job…//<portrait=happy>And here we are!
<PlayerName>$player</>, what’s your favorite kind of cookie?
Good choice! I’ll have to remember that.
Good choice! I’ll have to remember that.
Really? Me too! Red velvet everything for me, forever.
Oh. Well, um, I’ll…keep that in mind!
The smell of fresh baked goods can really liven up a place.
Do you like to go to the library?//Even if you’re not much of a reader, <NpcName>Millie</> has a lot of great insights.
I like to visit just to get her talking about something.//She seems so chill, but she can get really fired up.
I like to take inspiration from the beach sometimes.//<portrait=happy>The shells, the sea… So much material.
What’s your farmhouse like inside?//<portrait=happy>I’d love to see it sometime!//<portrait=normal>You can learn a lot about someone from their home.
Isn’t the lake beautiful in winter?//So placid… So still.
Winter makes everything look so different, doesn’t it?
<NpcName>Betty</> and I have this little ritual.//<portrait=normal>Every Sunday, one of us bakes a little cake, and we share it!
It’s important to have friends who share your interests, and to always make time for them.
Older people have the most amazing stories! I suppose when you live that long, it’s bound to happen.
*sighs* I want to lead a life that’s worth telling stories about, too.
I love it here.//<portrait=normal>It’s so peaceful…but so full of life, too.
I don’t have any free samples.//<portrait=concerned>We don’t do that here...sorry!
Although… Come to think of it, that’s not a bad idea!//<portrait=happy>I’ll talk to <NpcName>Sam</>.
I love the way Sam’s smells. Most stores smell weird, but we keep this place spick-and-span!
It’s a shame to stay inside all day, with weather like this.//<portrait=concerned>But I’m so busy, what choice do I have?
The weather report said it would be raining all day…//<portrait=concerned>And it was right! It’s still going out there.
<PlayerName>$player</>, do you like the rain?//<portrait=normal>I do. It casts everything in a new light, and it smells great.
Baking is a science as much as it is an art. It takes a lot of technical expertise to make the perfect bread.
But don’t let that discourage you!//Learning from your mistakes is half the fun of it.
Baking pays the bills, but it’s also something I’m passionate about!//<portrait=happy>So that’s a win-win.
I’m a real believer in the power of DIY.//It’s so fulfilling to make things yourself!
And it’s generally cheaper that way, too, which is a huge plus for me.
I think having a new face has been good for Starlet.//Fresh perspectives make everything better.
And it’s wonderful to see that farm flourishing again.//<portrait=normal>You’re doing great.
